[
    {
        "content": "<p>so today, this does not compile:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code> Str.toUtf8 &quot;Hi there!&quot; |&gt; Str.fromUtf8 == Ok &quot;Hi there!&quot;\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 345397243,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680095616
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>the reason is the precedence of <code>|&gt;</code> and <code>==</code></p>",
        "id": 345397430,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680095651
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/22008/7Lmzd3kMpNhJTL20dA4qC-ZY/Screen-Shot-2023-03-29-at-9.15.30-AM.png\">Screen-Shot-2023-03-29-at-9.15.30-AM.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/22008/7Lmzd3kMpNhJTL20dA4qC-ZY/Screen-Shot-2023-03-29-at-9.15.30-AM.png\" title=\"Screen-Shot-2023-03-29-at-9.15.30-AM.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/22008/7Lmzd3kMpNhJTL20dA4qC-ZY/Screen-Shot-2023-03-29-at-9.15.30-AM.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 345397727,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680095735
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>to get this to work, we have to put parens around the part before <code>==</code></p>",
        "id": 345397792,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680095752
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/22008/P2ZJP9rGqD48S6nRulPH33Kq/Screen-Shot-2023-03-29-at-9.15.58-AM.png\">Screen-Shot-2023-03-29-at-9.15.58-AM.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/22008/P2ZJP9rGqD48S6nRulPH33Kq/Screen-Shot-2023-03-29-at-9.15.58-AM.png\" title=\"Screen-Shot-2023-03-29-at-9.15.58-AM.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/22008/P2ZJP9rGqD48S6nRulPH33Kq/Screen-Shot-2023-03-29-at-9.15.58-AM.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 345397829,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680095762
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I can't think of a use case where this is the behavior we want</p>",
        "id": 345398431,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680095914
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What about?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>positions\n|&gt; List.keepIf \\pos -&gt; pos.x == 0\n|&gt; something\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 345398484,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1680095925
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>hm, I'd assume in that case the <code>==</code> would be inside the lambda <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>",
        "id": 345398569,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680095946
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'll give it a try!</p>",
        "id": 345398687,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680095972
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah ok. Yeah, I can't think of anything else</p>",
        "id": 345399099,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1680096073
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah that still works</p>",
        "id": 345399144,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680096086
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(if I change the precedence such that the original example works)</p>",
        "id": 345399206,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680096103
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For cases where I'd use <code>==</code> to construct a bool to pass as an argument to the piped function, I'd use parens anyway</p>",
        "id": 345399805,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1680096261
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Like in builder pattern:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>Button.new\n|&gt; Button.disabledIf (count == 0)\n|&gt; Button.view\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 345400317,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1680096386
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah I think the current way, if you use <code>|&gt;</code> and <code>==</code> you always get a type mismatch <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 345400492,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680096427
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>because you'll always either be trying to give too many arguments to <code>==</code> or else you'll be trying to run a <code>Bool</code> as a function</p>",
        "id": 345400588,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680096443
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Cool! I like this</p>",
        "id": 345401068,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1680096521
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would this extend to all comparison operators?</p>",
        "id": 345401431,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1680096593
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I might be missing something, but I think this would work for all infix operators</p>",
        "id": 345403095,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1680096930
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah I think <code>|&gt;</code> should probably just have the highest precedence <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>",
        "id": 345403305,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680096968
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Except for unary operators, right? I think <code>-a |&gt; b</code> should mean <code>(-a) |&gt; b</code> and not <code>-(a |&gt; b)</code></p>",
        "id": 345410270,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1680098357
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That might always be the case when mixing unary and infix. Not sure how the parser works.</p>",
        "id": 345410651,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1680098422
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh sure</p>",
        "id": 345411635,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680098611
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah I'm just talking about infix operators here</p>",
        "id": 345411656,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680098616
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Cool cool</p>",
        "id": 345413598,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1680098971
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Crazy question. With the change in precedence, would this work:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span><code>a\n|&gt; SomeTransform\n|&gt; == SomeResult\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 345560982,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1680150887
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note, <code>==</code>could theoretically be any other infix operator.</p>",
        "id": 345561034,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1680150934
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The fact that the |&gt; parts are on multiple lines, and the == is on the same line, make that read really strangly to me</p>",
        "id": 345753977,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1680199888
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If we want to reduce the precedence, IMO that really only makes sense if we start formatting it differently</p>",
        "id": 345754986,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1680200185
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right now, if you have a '+' operator somewhere in the middle of a pizza chain (with no parens), you'll get an error that one of the elements of that chain is not a function call (I think / assume?). If we just naively reduce the precedence, that + operator will be at the root of the tree - which will IMO be very unintuitive with the normal formatting</p>",
        "id": 345755458,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1680200335
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah I don't think <code>|&gt; ==</code> ought to work <span aria-label=\"big smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"big smile\">:big_smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 345776642,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680206937
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>in genearal I don't think we should allow multiple infix operators in a row</p>",
        "id": 345777578,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1680207220
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>x &lt; y &lt; z</code> can be pretty nice in some languages (as an equivalence for <code>x &lt; y &amp;&amp; y &lt; z</code>), but it admittedly doesn't come up very often, and there are usually additional rules to prevent someone from writing out-of-order expressions like <code>x &gt; y &lt; z</code></p>",
        "id": 346378707,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Gillette",
        "timestamp": 1680449788
    }
]